& [OperatorQuestion] is the bounded inquiry
  + [question] is identify the exact pressure-decomposition or local pressure projection statement needed to compare project pressure-tail components with local suitable solution pressure terms
  + [reason] is the previous mapping found conceptual slots but no operator-level bridge

& [OperatorSourceSet] is the resolved source neighborhood
  + [source_001_local_pressure_projection] is local pressure projection introduced for CKN-type results for local suitable weak solutions
    = source: On the local pressure of the Navier-Stokes equations and related systems
    = url: https://arxiv.org/pdf/1611.01482
    = role: primary operator target
    = reading: local pressure projection is the precise operator vocabulary for removing or localizing pressure in arbitrary cylindrical domains
    = project_use: compare each project pressure-tail component against the projection-generated local pressure and harmonic remainder terms
  + [source_002_wolf_local_suitable_frame] is local suitable weak solutions with local pressure decomposition p = partial_t p_h + p_0 in exposition
    = source: Local boundedness of local suitable weak solutions of the Navier-Stokes equations
    = url: https://sebastian-hensel.com/master_thesis.pdf
    = role: frame support
    = reading: the harmonic component p_h is not optional vocabulary; it is part of the local suitable solution structure
    = project_use: prevents treating harmonic pressure as generic tail debris
  + [source_003_projected_pressure_local_energy] is local energy weak solution framework with projected pressure
    = source: Local energy weak solutions for the Navier-Stokes equations in the half-space
    = url: https://arxiv.org/abs/1711.04486
    = role: secondary operator target
    = reading: projected pressure and pressure representation formulas are used to localize pressure behavior in local energy weak solution settings
    = project_use: fallback if Wolf-frame terms do not match the project pressure-tail route
  + [source_004_pressure_role_equivalence] is pressure-role regularity and dissipative/local suitable equivalence work
    = source: The role of the pressure in the regularity theory for the Navier-Stokes equations
    = url: https://www.research-collection.ethz.ch/bitstreams/1c1170b9-dc9d-4f74-a4d5-b8479bb403bf/download
    = role: authority-context support
    = reading: pressure definitions and solution classes matter for epsilon regularity and short-time local regularity
    = project_use: avoid mixing incompatible pressure notions across frames

